  "texts": [
    "If a parameter δ enters the computation, then the symbol C δ denotes constants that additionally depend on δ.",
    "On the contrary, precise constants that we refer to are denoted in a different way.We now provide assumptions on the data of the problem.",
    "(A1) α, τ and χ are positive constants.",
    "(A2) F = F 1 + F 2 satisfies: F 1: R → [0, +∞] is convex and lower semicontinuous withF 1 (0) = 0, while F 2 ∈ C 2 (R) has a Lipschitz continuous derivative F ′ 2.",
    "(A3) P ∈ C 0 (R) is nonnegative, bounded, and Lipschitz continuous."
